Editor's Note: In the face of the epidemic, it is necessary for all industries in China to work hand in hand to tide over difficulties, to record the experience of China Huaneng's company to assist the construction of Raytheon Mountain Hospital.

Faster. Faster.

Tianjin Girl Fang Xiaoyu was given the task of transporting 32.5 tons of square steel from Tianjin to Wuhan Junyun village, which is the square pipe needed for the construction of the ICU ward of Wuhan Raytheon Mountain Hospital.

On January 23, Wuhan's new pneumonia prevention and control headquarters announced that construction would begin at the same time at Caidian District and Jiangxia District in Wuhan, with the construction of about 1,000 beds at the Huoshenshan hospital to be put into operation on February 2; About 1,500 beds will be put into operation on February 5.

Hu Jun, general manager of China Huaneng's Shanghai e Commerce Company, and Wang Fei, business director, contacted China Construction Bureau 3, a supply chain partner of Huoshenshan and Raytheon, to communicate the material needs of the hospital. After learning of the need for square tubes for the ICU ward of Raytheon Mountain Hospital, Wang Fei found a batch of square tubes in Tianjin.

The task of transportation fell to Huaneng's Huaneng good luck platform, an O2o company in the logistics industry. Fang Xiaoyu is a good luck company in Tianjin Employees, heavy responsibility fell to her shoulders. She felt the urgency of the time, for her, the first time is to find a car.

Normally, finding a car would be easy. This is because over the past week or so, materials from all over the country are being urgently transported to Hubei epidemic areas such as Wuhan. It is the Spring Festival holiday, and most transport companies are just in a "half-closed" state. The transportation resources that can be mobilized are already limited, segregation exacerbated the lack of transport capacity.

At 11:14 pm on January 30(the sixth day of the Lunar New Year) , Fang Xiaoweixin contacted eight logistics companies he had worked with in the past, and three of them were available by telephone. Half an hour later, at 12:28, she was reassured by a promise that Fang Xiao could deliver the goods.

At about the same time, Cao Meng, Huaneng's lucky CEO, pulled a group together for Fang Xiaohe and the finance director. Cao Meng told the finance director to help with the payment. All the prep work is done. It's after 2:00 in the morning. Fang Xiao Yu found that the boss didn't rest until two o'clock.

The whole Spring Festival, Cao Meng in Shanghai had a New Year's Day, on the rush back to Wuxi, because the team in Wuxi good luck shunting. Throughout the Spring Festival holiday, by January 27, demand for the entire shipment had become very high. Cao Meng told the "deep net" that he has been looking for a variety of transport capacity, to Wuhan's material delivery in the past.

After transporting Tianjin Fanggang to Wuhan, Cao Meng entrusted all power to Fang Xiao. After four hours of sleep, the next morning, the chief financial officer was the first to get all the papers ready. All we need is the wind. Fang Xiaoyu was waiting for the bus to arrive in Tianjin, but the bus didn't come.

After 6 am on January 31st, Fang Xiaoyu got the message that the driver who promised to deliver the goods had changed his mind and his family would not let him go. Fang Xiaoyu was very understanding of the driver, the driver returned from Wuhan to quarantine for 14 days.

She continued to contact several other logistics companies, at 6:38 when the confirmed carrier vehicle, Hebei Master Zhou Zhihong.

After contacting the vehicle, Fang Xiaoyu began to implement the advance payment, because the financial controller had confirmed the payment procedure.

At 8:20, lucky employee Liu Jiantan arrived at the Zhongxing Storage and Transportation Center in Jinghai district of Tianjin. It took him 50 minutes to get a taxi from home. Liu Jiantan, 31, had just driven home to Tianjin on the evening of the 30th.

After Liu Jiantan arrived at the loading site, he inspected the goods in the warehouse and completed the docking with the factory contact, he began to prepare the loading documents, driver contract, payment proxy, loading details and other related materials.

"Dad's gone to support the plague. "

The truck driver was Zhou Zhihong, a 37-year-old from Dongguang County in Cangzhou, Hebei Province. Zhou Zhihong stayed at home throughout the Spring Festival. For Zhou Zhihong, who has been driving a big truck for 10 years, the 1,100-kilometer journey from Tianjin to Wuhan is not long, but the construction of the Thor Mountain Hospital is a matter of great importance.

He agreed to take the order, and at the same time, he made a mental decision not to tell his family where he was going so as not to worry them. Although Wuhan is an epidemic area, in Zhou's view, there are still ten million people in the city, it is impossible for everyone to be sick, and in the past he just unloaded a cargo.

Early in the morning, just after dawn, Zhou Zhihong set off from Cangzhou, Hebei Province, for Tianjin. At 12:40, he arrived at the loading site. Zhou Zhihong, Liu Jiantan and the warehouse two workers began loading master.

Everyone's in the Split Second.

"In the gap between the worker and the driver directing the car to reverse, I and another driver began to check the number of points. Since there were four and three square tubes in a bundle, we made a loading plan according to the vehicle's load and stability. One worker and the other driver controlled the crane while loading the car and recorded the number of pounds. The driver and I hung hooks and removed hooks from the car. Command Crane fine-tuning. " Liu Jiantan to "deep web" description.

At 13:07, when all the goods had been loaded, Liu Jiantan breathed a sigh of relief and looked around. They were the only one to load the goods that day, and they all wore masks during the process of loading and hurried home after loading the goods. At 14:07, Fang xiayu finished the payment for the goods and made the receipt according to the delivery list.

At 15 o'clock, Zhou Zhihong took all the documents and set off from the pick-up point, heading for the beijing-taiwan expressway. His route is the beijing-taipei expressway,-the Guangzhou-guangzhou expressway,-the Shanghai-lotus expressway,-the destination, a total of 1,100 km. He's got his hazmat suit, his mask, his gloves.

In China, there are too many truck drivers like Zhou Zhihong, who are responsible for more than 70 percent of freight traffic as they move along the country's roads. It was the wee hours of the morning, after ten hours of rolling and rolling roads. Perhaps because of the first month, the road is not many cars, the road is also good, but Zhou Zhihong is very sleepy.

When the truck arrived at the Cao County service station in Heze, Zhou Zhihong took a break, refueled, had a meal and had a short rest. He stayed for more than four hours. He wanted to sleep before he set off, but he received a notice on the way. The goods were very urgent, must Arrive on the afternoon of February 1st.

As the van pulled out of the Lotus highway and into Wuhan, he saw the inspector in a protective suit, and he felt a little nervous and uneasy, but it soon cleared up.

At 1 p.m. on Feb. 1, Zhou Zhihong's car arrived at the Junyun village in Wuhan. He drove 1,100 kilometers in 19 hours. He relaxed and felt that he had accomplished a task.

Zhou Zhihong has been driving a big truck for ten years. He feels that in the past, he is delivering goods. But this time, the steel is different. He felt that home can tell his family, he went to Wuhan, told the Children, "Dad went to support the epidemic area, not to run long distance. "

The 32.5 tons of steel needed for the hospital were shipped from Jinghai district in Tianjin to Junyun village in Wuhan in just 19 hours, a Split Second detail in the construction of the hospital. A few small details add up to explain why a hospital can be built in 10 days.

A hospital in ten days

On February 3rd, Vulcan Mountain Hospital was delivered. How is the construction of Thor Mountain Hospital going?

On February 2, the overall progress of the project in Wuhan's Raytheon Mountain Hospital was 65 percent complete. 60 per cent of the area of separation was completed, with 3,300 containers and 2,530 on-site, and about 60 per cent of the civil works were completed The construction of ground leveling, trench excavation, trench pipeline pre-embedding, trench backfilling, main pipeline surface layer pouring and PE membrane in non-trench area have all been completed.

The southwest corner, 20 km from the heart of Wuhan, is already a huge construction site, with the roar of machines, the sound of welding, and the Peaceful Huangjiahu Boulevard, where vehicles and goods are shuttled back and forth across the road, and the workers on the construction site.

CCTV is streaming live from the construction site of Mount Thor Hospital, one of the most watched buildings in the country. Hundreds of millions of people around the world are watching every second of hospital construction through 24-hour live webcasts.

China Construction Third Bureau is the contractor of the Raytheon Mountain Hospital. After receiving the order, Zhu Guosheng, deputy general manager of the Shandong Company, the First Construction Engineering Limited Liability Company of China Construction Third Bureau, said in an interview that, china Construction Third Bureau one company South China Company to support 120 sets of panels, with more than 3035-ton freight cars overnight to Wuhan.

Huadong Company transported 510 containers and 100 corridor boxes overnight. Western company undertook 210 standard boxes and 200 corridor boxes. Northern Company supported 1,134 box houses..

These materials include vehicle crane flat cars, forklifts, climbing cars, generators and other infrastructure tools, but also including plastic pipes, sanitary ware, distribution boxes, split air conditioning, ultraviolet sterilization lamps, electric heating sterilization units and other installation components. At the same time, the contractor of the Third Construction Bureau from the national construction workers to management personnel, also ready to Wuhan.

Zhu Guosheng said that at the construction site in Wuhan, the Engineering System is well organized, different companies according to their own characteristics, corresponding construction, respectively, treatment infrastructure, medical isolation zone, medical sewage treatment, indoor design, drainage, and so on. "We need unified command, division of Labor, and simultaneous manufacturing to ensure speed. "

Zhu's company, Shandong, is responsible for building 5,000 square meters of board rooms and supplying 1,134 box-type board rooms for the construction of the hospital. By optimizing the internal systems engineering, the construction period is greatly shortened and the speed is guaranteed.

"At the construction site, the construction team worked around the clock and never stopped working. Most of the employees of the Third Bureau of CCCC were from Hubei. Everyone was holding their breath and had to beat the epidemic at 'China speed, ' " Zhu said in an interview.

In addition, materials from all over the country are also gathering in Wuhan.

5,000 square meters board room, 2,134 sets of box board room, more than 1,500 tons of plate, 31.43 tons of high quality painted plate, 32.5 tons of square steel... these construction parts and materials, Split Second, from all over the country continue to arrive at Wuhan Fire Mountain, Thor Mountain Hospital.

Now, the Vulcan Mountain Hospital has been completed, the completion of the Thor Mountain Hospital is just around the corner.

At the same time, the contractor of the Third Construction Bureau from the national construction workers to management personnel, also ready to Wuhan.

Zhu Guosheng said that at the construction site in Wuhan, the Engineering System is well organized, different companies according to their own characteristics, corresponding construction, respectively, treatment infrastructure, medical isolation zone, medical sewage treatment, indoor design, drainage, and so on. "We need unified command, division of Labor, and simultaneous manufacturing to ensure speed. "

Zhu's company, Shandong, is responsible for building 5,000 square meters of board rooms and supplying 1,134 box-type board rooms for the construction of the hospital. By optimizing the internal systems engineering, the construction period is greatly shortened and the speed is guaranteed.

"At the construction site, the construction team worked around the clock and never stopped working. Most of the employees of the Third Bureau of CCCC were from Hubei. Everyone was holding their breath and had to beat the epidemic at 'China speed, ' " Zhu said in an interview.

In addition, materials from all over the country are also gathering in Wuhan.

5,000 square meters board room, 2,134 sets of box board room, more than 1,500 tons of plate, 31.43 tons of high quality painted plate, 32.5 tons of square steel... these construction parts and materials, Split Second, from all over the country continue to arrive at Wuhan Fire Mountain, Thor Mountain Hospital.

Now, the Vulcan Mountain Hospital has been completed, the completion of the Thor Mountain Hospital is just around the corner.
